quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  36,70,"To warn whoever is alive{1} and justify the word [i.e., decree] against the disbelievers.",1:[In heart and mind, i.e., the believers.]
  36,71,"Do they not see that We have created for them from what Our hands{1} have made, grazing livestock, and [then] they are their owners?",1:[See footnote to 2:19.]
  36,72,"And We have tamed them for them, so some of them they ride, and some of them they eat."
  37,55,"And he will look and see him{1} in the midst of the Hellfire.",1:[The companion who had tried to dissuade him from belief on earth.]
  37,56,"He will say, "
  37,57,"If not for the favor of my Lord, I would have been of those brought in [to Hell]."
  38,34,"And We certainly tried Solomon and placed on his throne a body;{1} then he returned.{2}",1:[Said to be a devil or a lifeless body (one without capability), but Allāh alone knows.],2:[To sovereignty and to Allāh in repentance.]
  38,35,"He said, "
  38,36,"So We subjected to him the wind blowing by his command, gently, wherever he directed,"
  39,19,"Then, is one who has deserved the decree of punishment [to be guided]? Then, can you save one who is in the Fire?"
  39,20,"But those who have feared their Lord - for them are chambers,{1} above them chambers built high, beneath which rivers flow. [This is] the promise of Allāh. Allāh does not fail in [His] promise.",1:[i.e., elevated rooms, dwellings or palaces.]
  39,21,"Do you not see that Allāh sends down rain from the sky and makes it flow as springs [and rivers] in the earth; then He produces thereby crops of varying colors; then they dry and you see them turned yellow; then He makes them [scattered] debris. Indeed in that is a reminder for those of understanding."
